\section*{CommonJavaJars - A Package with useful libraries for Java GUIs}

To reduce the package size of other R packages with Java GUIs and to reduce jar file conflicts,
this package provides a few commonly used Java libraries.

You should be able to load them by calling similar code 
as the following in the \texttt{.onLoad} function of your package:

<<echo=TRUE,eval=F>>=

classes <- system.file("java", package = "CommonJavaJars", lib.loc = NULL)
if (nchar(classes)) {
	.jaddClassPath(classes)
	jars <- grep(".*\\.jar", list.files(classes, full.names = TRUE), TRUE, value = TRUE)
	if (length(jars)) { 
		.jaddClassPath(jars)
	}		
}

@

